cssQuestions.Ans:
Pseudo classes are used to define the special state of an element. Pseudo elements are used to style specified parts of an element.
 Syntax of pseduoclass: selector:pseudo-class {property:value;}
 Syntax of pseudo element: selector::pseudo-element {property:value;}
 Example of pseudo class: a:hover {color: red;}
 Example of pseudo element: p::first-line {color: red;}
